{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "22", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "05", "S": "13"}}, "news": [{"title": "Retail, cafes & co-working spaces planned at revamped railway stations in Bengaluru", "para": "South Western Railway is seeking consultants for commercial use of new station spaces.  These spaces at KSR Bengaluru and Yeshwantpur will host retail and food outlets.  Office and co-working spaces are also being considered for these railway assets.  Nineteen other stations across the Bengaluru division will also see commercial development.  Investors will be onboarded through auctions after consultant evaluation of proposals.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/bengaluru-railway-stations-to-transform-with-retail-cafes-and-co-working-spaces/132554060?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2116044/132554060.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Bengaluru development body housing faces heat over fire safety violations", "para": "Many Bangalore Development Authority housing projects lack essential fire safety clearances. Residents in several complexes face risks from incomplete safety systems and missing approvals. The BDA Indraprastha complex has not received a fire no-objection certificate due to access issues. Other projects like Gunjur and Thippasandra also await their fire NOCs. The BDA is reportedly working to address these compliance and safety concerns.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/bda-housing-dangers-bengalurus-apartment-complexes-lacking-fire-safety-approvals/132553845?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1836566/132553845.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Pune cantonment board directs redevelopment as 100 buildings deemed unsafe", "para": "Around 100 decades-old buildings in Pune's Camp area are structurally unsafe.  The Pune Cantonment Board has directed owners to submit redevelopment plans for these properties.  Weakened structures pose a threat to occupants and pedestrians, especially during monsoon.  Disputes between landlords and tenants have delayed redevelopment efforts significantly.  Urgent redevelopment or repairs are necessary to eliminate the risk posed by these old houses.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/pune-cantonment-board-takes-action-100-buildings-declared-unsafe-for-redevelopment/132553817?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-3613140/132553817.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}